@startuml
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 12

title ValidatingAdmissionPolicy avec CEL (K8s 1.30 GA)

actor "User" as user

rectangle "kube-apiserver" as api #326CE5 {

  rectangle "Admission Chain" as chain {
    rectangle "1. Authentication" as auth #87CEEB
    rectangle "2. Authorization" as authz #87CEEB
    rectangle "3. Mutating\nAdmission" as mutate #FFD700
    rectangle "4. Schema\nValidation" as schema #FFD700
    rectangle "5. Validating\nAdmission" as validate #90EE90 {
      component "CEL Policy 1" as cel1
      component "CEL Policy 2" as cel2
      component "Webhook" as webhook
    }
    rectangle "6. etcd" as etcd #E6E6FA
  }
}

user -down-> auth
auth -down-> authz
authz -down-> mutate
mutate -down-> schema
schema -down-> validate
validate -down-> etcd

note right of validate
  **Avantages CEL vs Webhooks:**
  ✅ Pas de latence réseau
  ✅ Pas de dépendance externe
  ✅ Évaluation in-process
  ✅ Plus simple à déployer
  ✅ Audit natif
end note

note bottom
  **Exemple de règle CEL:**
  ```
  object.spec.replicas <= 10
  object.metadata.labels.exists(l, l == 'app')
  !object.spec.template.spec.containers.exists(
    c, c.securityContext.privileged == true
  )
  ```
end note

legend right
  |= Action |= Description |
  | Allow | Requête acceptée |
  | Deny | Requête rejetée |
  | Warn | Acceptée + warning |
  | Audit | Log uniquement |
endlegend

@enduml
